  "body": "# Rationale\r\n\r\nWhy should this feature exist?\r\nCurrently, we have `callTracer` with the option `withLog`. The result is the call frames with the logs inside each frame. Now I want to get the only logs, I need to recursive the result of the tracer and get the logs. It's not necessary.\r\n\r\nWhat are the use-cases?\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\nI want to create a new tracer named by `logTracer` to get the event logs. Maybe it will be duplicated some code with `callTracer` but the result is different.\r\n\r\nThe output looks like:\r\n```json\r\n[\r\n  {\r\n    \"address\": \"0x350e0ffc780a6a75b44cc52e1ff9092870668945\",\r\n    \"topics\": [\r\n      \"0xcacb62d8acea4678658eb5dc4aaa889b34d893b967c96a5f8c066e6549fa3f42\"\r\n    ],\r\n    \"data\": \"\"\r\n  },\r\n  {\r\n    \"address\": \"0x350e0ffc780a6a75b44cc52e1ff9092870668945\",\r\n    \"topics\": [\r\n      \"0xcacb62d8acea4678658eb5dc4aaa889b34d893b967c96a5f8c066e6549fa3f42\"\r\n    ],\r\n    \"data\": \"\"\r\n  }\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nDo you have ideas regarding the implementation of this feature?\r\nI only need to get the logs events instead of the all call frames.\r\nAre you willing to implement this feature?\r\nYes",
